lv.lumii.layoutengine

Class Label

  • java.lang.Object
    • lv.lumii.layoutengine.Element
      • lv.lumii.layoutengine.AbstractContainer
        • lv.lumii.layoutengine.Label
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    InsideLabel, OutsideLabel

    public abstract class Label
extends AbstractContainer
    The base class of all labels. Label can contain other labels.

      • _convertToInsideLabel

        public InsideLabel _convertToInsideLabel(AbstractContainer newOwner)
        Converts this label to an inside label belonging to the new owner. Copies all parameters and children. Does nothing if this label already is an inside label (not even changes the owner; that will be handled by the move operation).
        Parameters:
        newOwner - the owner of the new inside label.
        Returns:
        the new inside label, or this label if it already is an inside label

      • convertToInsideLabel

        public InsideLabel convertToInsideLabel(java.awt.geom.Point2D.Double newCenter,
                                        AbstractContainer newOwner,
                                        java.awt.geom.Point2D.Double growPoint)
        Converts this label to an inside label (if it wasn't already), then places it at the given position, along with its children. The actual size may differ due to children. The new owner of the label will be stretched to accommodate the label at its desired new position. The whole diagram is reordered afterwards, or at the end of the current transaction.
        Parameters:
        newCenter - the new desired center of the label
        newOwner - the new owner of the label
        growPoint - the exact point at which to insert the label, it will then be grow from that point to its desired position as per resize(java.awt.geom.Rectangle2D.Double)
        Returns:
        the new inside label, or this label if it already is an inside label

      • convertToInsideLabel

        public InsideLabel convertToInsideLabel(java.awt.geom.Point2D.Double newCenter,
                                        AbstractContainer newOwner,
                                        java.awt.geom.Point2D.Double growPoint,
                                        java.lang.Integer row,
                                        java.lang.Integer column)
        Converts this label to an inside label (if it wasn't already), then places it at the given position, along with its children. The actual size may differ due to children. The new owner of the label will be stretched to accommodate the label at its desired new position. The whole diagram is reordered afterwards, or at the end of the current transaction.
        Parameters:
        newCenter - the new desired center of the label
        newOwner - the new owner of the label
        growPoint - the exact point at which to insert the label, it will then be grow from that point to its desired position as per resize(java.awt.geom.Rectangle2D.Double)
        row - the row of the label in new owner's grid
        column - the column of the label in new owner's grid
        Returns:
        the new inside label, or this label if it already is an inside label

      • _convertToBoxOutsideLabel

        public OutsideLabel.BoxOutsideLabel _convertToBoxOutsideLabel(Box newOwner)
        Converts this label to a box outside label belonging to the new owner. Copies all parameters and children. Does nothing if this label already is a box outside label (not even changes the owner; that will be handled by the move operation).

      • convertToBoxOutsideLabel

        public OutsideLabel.BoxOutsideLabel convertToBoxOutsideLabel(java.awt.geom.Point2D.Double point,
                                                             Box box)
        Converts this label to a box outside label (if it wasn't already), then moves this box outside label to the given point onto the given box. The point is moved to the perimeter of the box if necessary. This operation can change this label's box side.
        Parameters:
        point - the point to move this label to. If this point is not on the perimeter of this label's box, it is moved there.
        box - the new box owner of this label
        Returns:
        the new box outside label, or this label if it already is a box outside label

      • convertToBoxOutsideLabel

        public OutsideLabel.BoxOutsideLabel convertToBoxOutsideLabel(Box.BoxSide side,
                                                             double position,
                                                             Box box)
        Converts this label to a box outside label (if it wasn't already), then moves this label to the given side of the given box at the given position.
        Parameters:
        side - the side of this labels box to move it to
        position - the position on this side to place the label at, as a proportion of the whole length of the side. Must be between 0 and 1, inclusive.
        box - the new box owner of this label
        Returns:
        the new box outside label, or this label if it already is a box outside label

      • convertToLineLabel

        public OutsideLabel.LineLabel convertToLineLabel(java.awt.geom.Point2D.Double point,
                                                 Line newOwner,
                                                 OutsideLabel.LineLabel.Orientation orientation)
        Converts this label to a line label (if it wasn't already), then moves this label to the given point on the given line. If the point is not on the line, first moves the point onto the line.
        Parameters:
        point - the point where to move this label
        newOwner - the line on which to place this label
        orientation - the orientation of the new line label
        Returns:
        the new line label, or this label if it already is a line label

      • convertToLineLabel

        public OutsideLabel.LineLabel convertToLineLabel(double position,
                                                 Line newOwner,
                                                 OutsideLabel.LineLabel.Orientation orientation)
        Converts this label to a line label (if it wasn't already), then moves this label to the given relative position on the given line.
        Parameters:
        position - the relative position where to place this label on the line (should be between 0 and 1, inclusive)
        newOwner - the line on which to place this label
        orientation - the orientation of the new line label
        Returns:
        the new line label, or this label if it already is a line label
